A diaphragm non‑return valve controls unidirectional fluid flow through a flexible diaphragm; when fluid moves forward the diaphragm lifts, allowing passage, while reverse flow forces the diaphragm against its seat, preventing backflow. This simple yet effective design safeguards pipelines and equipment from damage caused by reverse flow and minimizes the risk of cross‑contamination in sensitive process streams.
